'''不必要的醫療照顧'''（{{lang-en|Unnecessary health care}}）又稱'''過度治療'''、'''過度醫療'''（{{lang|en|overutilization、overuse、overtreatment}}），指的是提供的[[医疗卫生|醫療照顧]]份量或者是產生的成本，都高於應有的程度。<ref name="Perfect Storm">{{Cite journal|author=[[Ezekiel_J._Emanuel|Ezekiel J. Emanuel]], [[Victor_R._Fuchs|Victor R. Fuchs]]|title=The perfect storm of overutilization|journal=The Journal of the American Medical Association |volume=299|issue=23|pages=2789–91 |year=2008|doi=10.1001/jama.299.23.2789|pmid=18560006|url=http://www.ipalc.org/Healthcare_Policy/The%20Perfect%20Storm%20of%20Overutilization%20%28JAMA%202008%29.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090902053119/http://www.ipalc.org/Healthcare_Policy/The%20Perfect%20Storm%20of%20Overutilization%20%28JAMA%202008%29.pdf|archive-date=2009-09-02}}</ref>在美國，醫療衛生成本佔GDP的比例，是[[已開發國家|已開發國家]]中最高，過度使用是造成這種高支出的主要原因，估計在2012年，過度使用約佔其醫療衛生支出的三分之一（2.6兆美元中的7,500億美元）。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Kliff|first1=Sarah|title=We spend $750 billion on unnecessary health care. Two charts explain why.|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2012/09/07/we-spend-750-billion-on-unnecessary-health-care-two-charts-explain-why/|access-date=2016-03-31|work=The Washington Post|date=2012-09-07|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151230122254/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/wonk/wp/2012/09/07/we-spend-750-billion-on-unnecessary-health-care-two-charts-explain-why/|archive-date=2015-12-30}}</ref>
 
導致過度使用的因素包括：要求[[醫事人員|醫事人員]]做更多的事，因此要支付更多的錢（[[按服務收費|按服務收費]]支付模式）、擔心有日後訴訟而多做[[防禦性醫療|防禦性醫療]]、消費者不是付款人（無論是由公共保險，私人保險，或是兩者代患者支付），不會產生[[需求的價格彈性|需求的價格彈性]]的結果。<ref>{{cite journal|author=[[Ezekiel_J._Emanuel|Ezekiel J. Emanuel]] & [[Victor_R._Fuchs|Victor R. Fuchs]]|title=Health Care Overutilization in the United States—Reply|journal=The Journal of the American Medical Association| volume=300|issue=19|page=2251|doi=10.1001/jama.2008.605|year=2008}}</ref>這些因素導致[[醫療系統|醫療系統]]中的各方（醫生、患者、藥廠、設備製造商）都缺乏約束醫療衛生價格的足夠動機，因此無法控制過度使用。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/><ref name="Waste"/>付款人（例如[[國家健康保險|國民健康保險]]系統，或是{{link-en|聯邦醫療保險和聯邦醫療補助服務中心|Center for Medicare and Medicaid Innovation}}（CMS））會強調根據[[醫療必要性|醫療必要性]]作為付款的條件。但是，必要與否之間的分際，存有相當的主觀性。
 
嚴格來說，過度治療是指不必要的醫學干預，包括對可自癒疾病的治療（{{link-en|過度診斷|overdiagnosis}}），或對僅需有限治療的疾病給予廣泛的治療。
 
從經濟上講，它與過度[[醫療化|醫療化]]有關。

==定義==
這個名詞是由{{link-en|約翰·溫伯格|John Wennberg}}所說的{{link-en|不合理的變異|unwarranted variation}}蛻變而來，<ref name="MoreIsLess">{{cite news |title=More is Less |author=Alix Spiegel |newspaper=[[This_American_Life|This American Life]] |date=2009-11-10 |url=http://www.thisamericanlife.org/radio-archives/episode/391/more-is-less |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105005053/http://www.thisamericanlife.org/radio-archives/episode/391/more-is-less |archivedate=2011-11-05 |accessdate=2020-09-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>不同的治療方式是根據人們居住的區域，而不是根據臨床標準而發生。他在1967年的研究發現這種情況，並在1970年代和1980年代發表："基本前提-所謂醫學是科學，由醫生依據公認的事實和理論做出臨床決定來執行，但實際上與我們所看到的數據不符。很明顯的，[[醫療衛生提供者|醫療衛生提供者]]在推動需求方面，比之前我們所知的有更大的影響力。"<ref>Michael T. McCue [http://www.managedhealthcareexecutive.com/mhe/article/articleDetail.jsp?id=46508 Clamping down on variation] {{Wayback|url=http://www.managedhealthcareexecutive.com/mhe/article/articleDetail.jsp?id=46508 |date=20071218052952 }} - Managed Healthcare Executive, February 01, 2003</ref>
 
2008年，美國[[生物倫理學|生物倫理學]]家{{link-en|Ezekiel J. Emanuel|Ezekiel Emanuel}}和[[健康經濟學|健康經濟學]]家{{link-en|Victor R. Fuchs|Victor Fuchs}}將不必要的醫療照顧定義為"過度利用"，即提供的服務份量或者成本都比適當的為高。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/>最近，經濟學家試圖從錯誤消費而非從[[過度消耗|過度消費]]的角度來談論不必要的醫療照顧。<ref>{{Cite journal|last1=Hensher|first1=Martin|last2=Tisdell|first2=John|last3=Zimitat|first3=Craig|date=2017-03-01|title="Too much medicine": Insights and explanations from economic theory and research|journal=Social Science & Medicine|volume=176|pages=77–84|doi=10.1016/j.socscimed.2017.01.020|pmid=28131024|url=https://eprints.utas.edu.au/23729/1/Hensher%20Too%20Much%20Medicine%20PrePrint%20260817.pdf|access-date=2020-09-14|archive-date=2018-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719031307/https://eprints.utas.edu.au/23729/1/Hensher%20Too%20Much%20Medicine%20PrePrint%20260817.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>
 
在2009年，兩名美國醫生在一篇社論中寫道，不必要的醫療照顧"可定義為對患者沒有明顯好處的服務"，它可能佔美國醫療衛生服務的30％。<ref name="MuchAdo">{{cite journal|vauthors=Reilly BM, Evans AT | s2cid=12934288| title=Much ado about (doing) nothing| journal=[[Ann_Intern_Med|Ann Intern Med]] | year= 2009 | volume= 150 | issue= 4 | pages= 270–1 | pmc= | pmid=19221379 | doi=10.7326/0003-4819-150-4-200902170-00008| citeseerx=10.1.1.688.1277}} {{subscription}}</ref>他們提到2003年有關醫療衛生支出有區域差異的研究，研究發現："[[聯邦醫療保險|聯邦醫療保險]]（Medicare）支出較高的地區，患者比支出較低的地區的享有更多的護理，但並沒產生較好的健康結果或較高的滿意度。"<ref>{{cite journal | pmid = 12585826 | doi=10.7326/0003-4819-138-4-200302180-00007 | volume=138 | issue=4 | title=The implications of regional variations in Medicare spending. Part 2: health outcomes and satisfaction with care | date=February 2003 | author=Fisher ES, Wennberg DE, [[Thérèse_Stukel|Stukel TA]], Gottlieb DJ, Lucas FL, Pinder EL | s2cid=8031637 | journal=Ann. Intern. Med. | pages=288–98}}</ref>

2012年1月，[[美國醫師學會|美國醫師學會]]的倫理，專業和人權委員會建議，與'簡約護理'相比，過度治療可作為簡約護理的反義詞，簡約護理是"利用最有效的手段，有效的診斷，來治療病症。" <ref>{{cite journal | author = Snyder L | s2cid = 207536403 | year = 2012 | title = American College of Physicians Ethics Manual: sixth edition | url = | journal = Ann Intern Med | volume = 156 | issue = 1 Pt 2| pages = 73–104 | doi = 10.7326/0003-4819-156-1-201201031-00001 | pmid = 22213573 }}</ref>
 
2012年4月，醫療衛生改進研究所的{{link-en|唐·貝里克|Donald Berwick}}和[[智庫|智庫]][[蘭德公司|蘭德公司]]的Andrew Hackbarth把過度治療定義為"無視合理的科學和患者自己的偏好，讓患者接受那些對他們無助的護理-而這些護理是植根於過時的護理習慣、供應導向行為、和對科學的漠視。"他們寫道，"試圖為所有的患者做某件事（治療或測試），不可避免的會施加到不需要的患者身上。" 在情況不確定的時候，"臨床{{link-en|最佳決策|optimal decision}}就會產生某些無實益的醫療照顧的副產品。"<ref>{{cite journal | author = Berwick DM, Hackbarth AD | date = Apr 2012 | title = Eliminating waste in US health care | url = | journal = JAMA | volume = 307 | issue = 14| pages = 1513–6 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2012.362 | pmid = 22419800 }}</ref>
 
在2015年10月，兩名[[小兒科|小兒科]]醫生表示，把"過度治療當作一種違反道德的行為"，有助於分辨醫事人員在治療或者不治療兩種衝突性動機的所在。<ref>{{cite journal | author = Ralston Shawn L., Schroeder Alan R. | year = 2015 | title = Doing More vs Doing Good: Aligning Our Ethical Principles From the Personal to the Societal | journal = JAMA Pediatrics | volume = 169 | issue =  12| pages = 1085–6 | doi = 10.1001/jamapediatrics.2015.2702 | pmid = 26502277 }} {{subscription}}</ref>

==醫療衛生費用==
美國是全球人均醫療衛生支出最高的國家，與其他國家/地區的患者相比，患者去醫院看病的次數較少，住院天數也較少，<ref name="vox">{{Cite news |url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2017/10/16/16357790/health-care-prices-problem |title=The problem is the prices |last=Kliff |first=Sarah |date=2017-10-16 |access-date=2018-12-07 |archive-date=2019-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191112104510/https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2017/10/16/16357790/health-care-prices-problem }}</ref>但價格高昂，<ref name="cfund">{{Cite web |url=https://www.commonwealthfund.org/publications/issue-briefs/2015/oct/us-health-care-global-perspective |title=Spending, Use of Services, Prices, and Health in 13 Countries |website=www.commonwealthfund.org |language=en |access-date=2018-12-07 |archive-date=2019-11-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110012617/https://www.commonwealthfund.org/publications/issue-briefs/2015/oct/us-health-care-global-perspective }}</ref>一些療程和新藥的使用比其他地方多，醫生的待遇是其他國家的兩倍。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/>[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]報導"沒人能確定"美國有多少不必要的醫療照顧。<ref name="MayDoLittle">{{cite news |title=Law May Do Little to Help Curb Unnecessary Care |author=Gina Colata |newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=2010-03-29 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/30/health/30use.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716030707/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/30/health/30use.html |archivedate=2017-07-16 |accessdate=2020-09-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>過度使用已經不再在醫療總支有大的佔比，2016年的美國醫療總支出是3.3兆美元。<ref name="nhe"/>，在2018年則是3.6兆美元。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/NationalHealthAccountsHistorical |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-09-14 |archive-date=2019-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191111221743/https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/NationalHealthAccountsHistorical.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
 
2014年，研究人員透過網站{{link-en|明智選擇|Choosing Wisely}}以及其他來源，對許多被列為價值不高的服務做分析。他們查看2008-2009年的支出情況，發現這些服務佔Medicare費用的0.6％或是2.7％<ref name="mcwilliams">{{Cite journal |last1=McWilliams |first1=J. Michael |last2=Chernew |first2=Michael E. |last3=Elshaug |first3=Adam G. |last4=Landon |first4=Bruce E. |last5=Schwartz |first5=Aaron L. |date=2014-07-01 |title=Measuring Low-Value Care in Medicare |journal=JAMA Internal Medicine |language=en |volume=174 |issue=7 |pages=1067–1076 |doi=10.1001/jamainternmed.2014.1541 |pmid=24819824 |pmc=4241845 |issn=2168-6106}}</ref>，要求做這些低價值服務的醫生沒有明顯的模式。<ref name="mcwilliams2018">{{Cite journal |last1=McWilliams |first1=J. Michael |last2=Zaslavsky |first2=Alan M. |last3=Jena |first3=Anupam B. |last4=Schwartz |first4=Aaron L. |date=2018-12-03 |title=Analysis of Physician Variation in Provision of Low-Value Services |journal=JAMA Internal Medicine |volume=179 |issue=1 |pages=16–25 |language=en |doi=10.1001/jamainternmed.2018.5086|pmid=30508010 |pmc=6583417 }}</ref>[[美國國家醫學院|美國國家醫學院]]（IOM）在2010年使用不同的方法對"不必要的醫療照顧"做出兩種估算：醫療支出（2.6兆美元<ref name="nhe">{{Cite web |url=https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/Downloads/Tables.zip |title=Table 1 National Health Expenditures |website=www.cms.gov |access-date=2018-12-05 |archive-date=2019-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919154113/https://www.cms.gov/Research-Statistics-Data-and-Systems/Statistics-Trends-and-Reports/NationalHealthExpendData/Downloads/Tables.zip |dead-url=no }}</ref>）的0.2％，或者是1％至5％，<ref name="iom2010">{{Cite book |url=https://www.nap.edu/read/12750/chapter/5 |title=The Healthcare Imperative: Lowering Costs and Improving Outcomes: Workshop Series Summary |last=Institute of Medicine |date=2010 |website=National Academies Press, (their $5 billion figure was 0.2% of total health expenditure) |language=en |access-date=2018-12-07 |doi=10.17226/12750 |pmid=21595114 |isbn=978-0-309-14433-9 |archive-date=2019-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191122221754/https://www.nap.edu/read/12750/chapter/5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>IOM在2012年的報告中引用2010年的報告，來解釋這個8％的不必要醫療照顧的估算數字（2,100億美元），但沒有解釋兩年數字的差異原因。<ref name="iom2012">{{Cite book |chapter-url=https://www.nap.edu/login.php?record_id=13444 |title=Best Care at Lower Cost: The Path to Continuously Learning Health Care in America |publisher=The National Academies Press |isbn=978-0-309-26073-2 |pages=101–102 |doi=10.1109/ipdps.2000.846027 |chapter=Replicating the contents of a WWW multimedia repository to minimize download time |year=2000 |last1=Loukopoulos |first1=T. |last2=Ahmad |first2=I. |s2cid=9998202 |access-date=2020-09-14 |archive-date=2021-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210418163019/https://www.nap.edu/login.php?record_id=13444 }}</ref>IOM的2012年報告還說，還有5,550億美元的其他浪費支出，和前述2,100億美元的浪費之間存在"未知的重疊"。<ref name="iom2012"/>
 
IOM在2005年估計（並未提出估計方法或資料來源），"在醫療衛生的費用，每花1美元，就有0.30到0.40美元是花費在品質低下的服務上"，相當於 "每年浪費超過五千億美元...浪費在過度使用、使用不足、濫用、重複、系統故障、不必要的重複、溝通不暢、和效率低下。"<ref>{{cite book |title=Building a Better Delivery System: A New Engineering/Health Care Partnership – Bridging the Quality Chasm |last=Lawrence |first=David |year=2005 |publisher=[[United_States_National_Academy_of_Sciences|National Academy of Sciences]] |location=Washington, DC |isbn=978-0-309-65406-7 |page=99 |url=http://www.nap.edu/catalog/11378.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080709002402/http://www.nap.edu/catalog/11378.html |archivedate=2008-07-09 |doi=10.17226/11378 |pmid=20669457 |access-date=2020-09-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2003年由Elliott S. Fisher等人發表的文章<ref name="Part1">{{Cite journal | author = [[Elliott_S._Fisher|Elliott S. Fisher]], [[David_E._Wennberg|David E. Wennberg]], [[Thérèse_Stukel|Thérèse A. Stukel]], [[Daniel_J._Gottlieb|Daniel J. Gottlieb]], [[F._L._Lucas|F. L. Lucas]] & [[Etoile_L._Pinder|Etoile L. Pinder]] | s2cid = 27581938 | title = The implications of regional variations in Medicare spending. Part 1: the content, quality, and accessibility of care | journal = [[Annals_of_Internal_Medicine|Annals of Internal Medicine]] | volume = 138 | issue = 4 | pages = 273–287 | date = February 2003 | pmid = 12585825 | doi = 10.7326/0003-4819-138-4-200302180-00006 | df = mdy-all }}</ref><ref name="Part2">{{Cite journal | author = [[Elliott_S._Fisher|Elliott S. Fisher]], [[David_E._Wennberg|David E. Wennberg]], [[Therese_A._Stukel|Therese A. Stukel]], [[Daniel_J._Gottlieb|Daniel J. Gottlieb]], [[F._L._Lucas|F. L. Lucas]] & [[Etoile_L._Pinder|Etoile L. Pinder]] | s2cid = 8031637 | title = The implications of regional variations in Medicare spending. Part 2: health outcomes and satisfaction with care | journal = [[Annals_of_Internal_Medicine|Annals of Internal Medicine]] | volume = 138 | issue = 4 | pages = 288–298 | date = February 2003 | pmid = 12585826 | doi = 10.7326/0003-4819-138-4-200302180-00007 | df = mdy-all }}</ref>，他們發現"對於各地區享有Medicare的患者來說，無論是在住院、外科手術、還是在醫院內進行診治，做得更多，但仍不能顯示明確的健康利益。" <ref name="Reflections">{{Cite journal | author=Steven A. Schroeder | title = Personal reflections on the high cost of American medical care: Many causes but few politically sustainable solutions | journal=[[Archives_of_Internal_Medicine|Archives of Internal Medicine]] | volume = 171 | issue = 8 | pages = 722–727 |date=April 2011 | doi = 10.1001/archinternmed.2011.149 | pmid = 21518938| author-link = Steven A. Schroeder }}</ref>在2003年，在不傷害患者的前提下，Medicare支出最多可削減30％。<ref name="Part2"/>
 
如果過度使用醫療照顧，患者會面臨到不必要併發症的風險，<ref name="Biden">{{cite news |title=Medicare Options In Biden Budget Talks Get Boost |newspaper=[[NPR|NPR]] |publisher=[[The_Associated_Press|The Associated Press]] |date=2011-06-15 |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=137200637 |accessdate=2011-06-26}}</ref>有記錄顯示過度使用手術和其他治療方法會對患者造成傷害。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Gibson |last2=Singh |first2=Rosemary |title=The Treatment Trap: How the Overuse of Medical Care is Wrecking Your Health |url=https://archive.org/details/treatmenttraphow00gibs/page/63 |year=2010 |publisher=Ivan R. Dee |location=Chicago |isbn=9781566638425 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/treatmenttraphow00gibs/page/63 63–83] }}</ref>

==肇因==
醫生的決定是不必要的醫療照顧的{{link-en|近因|proximate cause}}，但是他們做這種決定的時候，會受到潛在動機，以及可能遭受的懲罰所影響。
 
===第三方付款人和按服務收費===
{{see|按服務收費}}

當公共或私人保險機構利用按服務收費方式支付給醫生的時候，就可能有人不會考慮考慮到治療費用。第三方支付，還有按服務收費這兩種做法都有造成浪費的可能。<ref name="Waste">{{Cite journal | author=Victor R. Fuchs | title = Eliminating 'waste' in health care | journal=[[JAMA:_The_Journal_of_the_American_Medical_Association|JAMA: The Journal of the American Medical Association]] | volume = 302 | issue = 22 | pages = 2481–2482 |date=December 2009 | doi = 10.1001/jama.2009.1821 | pmid = 19996406| author-link = Victor R. Fuchs }}</ref>按服務收費產生過度使用的龐大誘因，因為醫療衛生提供者（例如醫生和醫院）可透過過度治療而獲得額外收入。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/>
 
[[阿圖·葛文德|阿圖·葛文德]]於2009年在《[[紐約客|紐約客]]》雜誌上發表他對[[麥卡倫_(得克薩斯州)|德州麥卡倫市]]Medicare按服務收費報銷調查的結果。<ref>{{cite news |title=Texas town's healthcare puzzle |author=Katty Kay |newspaper=BBC News |date=2009-07-07 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8137085.stm |accessdate=2011-06-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100216214634/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8137085.stm |archivedate=2010-02-16 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | author=Bryant Furlow | title = US reimbursement systems encourage fraud and overutilisation | journal=[[The_Lancet_Oncology|The Lancet Oncology]] | volume = 10 | issue = 10 | pages = 937–938 |date=October 2009 | pmid = 19810157 | doi = 10.1016/S1470-2045(09)70297-9| author-link = Bryant Furlow }}</ref>在Medicare的費用報銷，麥卡倫市在2006年的排名僅次於[[邁阿密|邁阿密]]，為美國的第二高。每個患者的費用幾乎是全國平均水準的兩倍。<ref name="Conundrum">{{cite news |title=The Cost Conundrum – What a Texas town can teach us about health care |author=Atul Gawande |newspaper=The New Yorker |date=2009-06-01 |url=http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2009/06/01/090601fa_fact_gawande?currentPage=all |accessdate=2011-06-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110610174307/http://www.newyorker.com/reporting/2009/06/01/090601fa_fact_gawande?currentPage=all |archivedate=2011-06-10 |author-link=Atul Gawande |dead-url=no }}</ref>

然而在1992年，麥卡倫市的醫療費用幾乎和Medicare的全國平均支出相同。<ref name="Conundrum"/>在查看其他可能的原因（例如當地人的健康狀況比較差，或者有醫療事故）之後，葛文德認為麥卡倫市是一個過度使用醫療服務的例子，<ref name="SpendMore">{{cite news |title=Spend More, Get Less? The Health Care 'Conundrum' |newspaper=[[Fresh_Air|Fresh Air]] |publisher=[[NPR|NPR]] |date=2009-06-17 |url=https://www.npr.org/templates/transcript/transcript.php?storyId=105483669 |accessdate=2011-06-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328041112/http://www.npr.org/templates/transcript/transcript.php?storyId=105483669 |archivedate=2014-03-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>他的結論是，麥卡倫市當地醫療機構的商業文化是把醫療服務當作賺取收入的來源，與[[梅奧醫院|梅奧醫院]]，還有在[[大章克申_(科羅拉多州)|科羅拉多州大章克申市]]醫療市場上的低成本，高品質醫學文化形成鮮明對比。<ref name="Conundrum"/><ref name="SpendMore"/> 葛文德建議：

{{quotation|隨著美國努力在擴大醫療保險的覆蓋範圍，同時又要控制醫療費用，我們現在面臨的決定，比我們是否擁有公共保險選項、或是我們終將擁有長期[[單一支付者醫療衛生系統|單一支付者醫療衛生系統]]、還是公共與私人保險的混合組成，更為重要。重要的是我們是否要獎勵那些試圖建立新一代，像梅奧醫院和大章克申市地區醫療機構的領導人。如果我們不這樣做，麥卡倫市將不會是一個[[離群值|離群值]]（極少數的案例），我們的未來可能就會變成這樣。<ref name="Conundrum"/>}}

===醫療事故法和防禦性醫學===
{{see also|醫療事故}}

美國醫生為了保護自己免受法律起訴，是有要求進行不必要的臨床檢查或者實際作用不大的檢查的動機。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/>防禦性醫學是被用來解釋高昂醫療費用的首選原因，但根據阿圖·葛文德估計，防禦性醫學在2010年僅占美國醫療衛生總支出2.3兆美元的2.4％。<ref name="Reflections"/><ref>{{Cite journal | author=Michelle M. Mello, Amitabh Chandra, Atul A. Gawande & David M. Studdert | title = National costs of the medical liability system| journal=[[Health_Affairs_(Project_Hope)|Health Affairs (Project Hope)]] | volume = 29 | issue = 9 | pages = 1569–1577 |date=September 2010 | doi = 10.1377/hlthaff.2009.0807 | pmid = 20820010 | pmc=3048809}}</ref>
 
===直接對消費者作廣告===
直接對於消費者作廣告會鼓勵患者採用藥物、器械、診斷方法、或者療程。有時，服務提供者會直接提供這些治療或服務，而不是花費心思，試圖說服患者說這些並不需要，或甚至是結果可能是弊大於利。<ref name="Perfect Storm"/>
 
===醫師的傾向===
[[達特茅斯學院|達特茅斯學院]]的{{link-en|Geisel醫學院|Geisel School of Medicine}}教授{{link-en|吉爾伯特·韋爾奇|H. Gilbert Welch}}在2016年指出，醫生和公眾的某些傾向可能會產生不必要的醫療照顧，例如：<ref>Gilbert Welch [https://www.acponline.org/sites/default/files/documents/about_acp/chapters/ut/16mtg/welch.pdf Assumptions That Drive Too Much Medical Care] American College of Physicians, n.d., retrieved 9 May 2018</ref><ref>{{cite book| title=Less Medicine, More Health |author=Gilbert Welch |year=2016 |publisher=Beacon Press |isbn=978-0807077580 }}</ref>
 
*只想到嘗試降低風險，而沒想到潛在利益甚微，或甚至是沒有
*只想解決問題，而不使用風險較低的檢測，或是順應的策略
*只想行動迅速，而事實上是利用等待，以得到更多資訊，可能更為明智
*沒考慮用"無作為"的做法
*低估運用診斷測試的不利之處
*未思考新療法的成本或舊療法的有效性，就採用新法，揚棄舊法
*為延長患者生命，但未顧及健康品質就提供治療，不探究患者自己的想法

==舉例==
===成像===
過度使用[[影像診斷學|影像診斷]]（如[[X射線|X射線]]和[[X射線電腦斷層掃描|CT掃描]]）被評斷為無法改善患者的護理結果。<ref name="Globally">{{Cite journal | author=B. Rehani | title = Imaging overutilisation: Is enough being done globally? | journal=[[Biomedical_Imaging_and_Intervention_Journal|Biomedical Imaging and Intervention Journal]] | volume = 7 | issue = 1 | pages = e6 |date=January 2011 | doi = 10.2349/biij.7.1.e6 | pmid = 21655115 | pmc = 3107688| author-link = B. Rehani | doi-broken-date = 2020-08-31 }}</ref>導致過度的因素包括" [[醫師自我推薦|醫師自我推薦]]、患者自己的意願、不妥適的經濟動機、衛生系統因素、產業、媒體、缺乏認知、還有防禦性醫療。"<ref name="Globally"/>有幾家著名組織，例如{{link-en|美國影像診斷學院|American College of Radiology}}（ACR）、{{link-en|英國皇家影像診斷學院|Royal College of Radiologists}}（RCR）、和[[世界衛生組織|世界衛生組織]]（WHO），就此而共同制定"適當性標準（appropriateness criteria）"以供參考。<ref name="Globally"/>加拿大影像診斷醫生協會在2009年估計，[[加拿大|加拿大]]的醫療系統有30%的影像診斷屬於多餘。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.car.ca/uploads/patient%20info/car_cat_scan_eng.pdf |title=Do you need that scan? |year=2009 |publisher=[[Canadian_Association_of_Radiologists|Canadian Association of Radiologists]] |accessdate=2011-06-27 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110322052940/http://www.car.ca/uploads/patient%20info/car_cat_scan_eng.pdf |archivedate=2011-03-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>2008年Medicare報銷顯示胸部CT掃描被過度使用。<ref>{{cite news |title=Medicare Claims Show Overuse for CT Scanning |author1=Walt Bogdanich |author2=Jo Craven McGinty |newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |date=2011-06-17 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/18/health/18radiation.html?_r=2&pagewanted=all |accessdate=2011-06-22 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zcfYCb5l?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/18/health/18radiation.html?_r=2&pagewanted=all |archivedate=2011-06-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>經濟動機被顯示是影響到牙醫使用更多X射線成像的原因，牙醫因為要求做這種成像可得到額外的收費。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Chalkley|first1=M.|last2=Listl|first2=S.|title=First do no harm – The impact of financial incentives on dental X-rays|journal=Journal of Health Economics|date=2017-12-30|doi=10.1016/j.jhealeco.2017.12.005|pmid=29408150|volume=58|issue=March 2018|pages=1–9|url=http://eprints.whiterose.ac.uk/135410/1/CHERP143_impact_financial_incentives_dental_xrays.pdf|access-date=2020-09-14|archive-date=2022-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119020758/https://eprints.whiterose.ac.uk/135410/1/CHERP143_impact_financial_incentives_dental_xrays.pdf}}</ref>
 
過度使用影像診斷會導致診斷出原本無關重要的疾病（請參考過度診斷（overdiagnosis））。<ref>{{Cite journal | author=Elm Ho | title = Overuse, overdose, overdiagnosis... overreaction? | journal=[[Biomedical_Imaging_and_Intervention_Journal|Biomedical Imaging and Intervention Journal]] | volume = 6 | issue = 3 | pages = e8 |date=July 2010 | doi = 10.2349/biij.6.3.e8 | pmid = 21611049 | pmc = 3097773| author-link = Elm Ho }}</ref>
 
====醫師自我推薦====
{{main|醫師自我推薦}}

有種過度使用的類型是醫生自我推薦。<ref name="Turf">{{Cite journal
 | author=[[David_C._Levin|David C. Levin]] & [[Vijay_M._Rao|Vijay M. Rao]]
 | title = Turf wars in radiology: the overutilization of imaging resulting from self-referral
 | journal=[[Journal_of_the_American_College_of_Radiology|Journal of the American College of Radiology]]
 | volume = 1
 | issue = 3
 | pages = 169–172
 |date=March 2004
 | doi = 10.1016/j.jacr.2003.12.009
 | pmid = 17411553
}}</ref>
多項研究不斷發現同一件事，即當一位非影像診斷醫生對放射線影像設備有經濟關係，而且有機會推薦的話，這些醫生的成像使用量就會不必要的增加。<ref name="Turf"/>美國成像使用的增長（是增長最快的醫師服務）大部分是非影像診斷醫師的自我推薦所產生。<ref name="Turf"/>在 2004年，這種過度使用估計讓美國年度醫療衛生費用花費160億美元。<ref name="Turf"/>截至2018年的審查證據顯示，在[[小兒科|小兒科]]的過度治療、過度醫療化、和過度診斷，包括有[[靜脈注射|靜脈注射]]補充體液、[[抗抑鬱藥|抗抑鬱藥]]、[[腸道外營養|腸道外營養]]、過度使用計劃提前分娩、腳踝受傷後的固定、使用水解嬰兒配方食品、對從{{link-en|細支氣管炎|bronchiolitis}}恢復的兒童有{{link-en|低血氧症|hypoxemia}}的過度診斷。<ref>{{cite journal | doi = 10.1001/jamapediatrics.2017.5752 | volume=172 | title=2017 Update on Pediatric Medical Overuse | year=2018 | journal=JAMA Pediatrics | author=Coon Eric R., Young Paul C., Quinonez Ricardo A., Morgan Daniel J., Dhruva Sanket S., Schroeder Alan R.| s2cid=4369253 | issue=5 | pages=482–486 | pmid=29582079 }}</ref>

